==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|punischen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}}, {{etyl|fro|en}} ''puniss-'', stem of some of the conjugated forms of {{m|fro|punir}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|punio|puniō, punīre|to inflict punishment upon|lang=la}}, from {{term|poena||punishment, penalty}}; see {{term|pain}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈpʌnɪʃ/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-punish.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|es}}

# To [[cause]] to [[suffer]] for [[crime]] or [[misconduct]], to [[administer]] [[disciplinary]] [[action]].
# To cause great [[harm]] to (''a punishing blow'').
# To [[dumb down]] severely or to the point of uselessness or near-uselessness.

====Synonyms====
